paragraphs.text:
%pyspark
from pyspark.sql import SQLContext
sqlContext = SQLContext(sc)

usdaDataFrame = sqlContext.read.format('com.databricks.spark.csv') \
    .options(header='true', inferschema='true') \
    .load('s3://cdphp-s3-us-e-l-dm/temp/HiveTemp/USDA.csv')

%pyspark
df = usdaDataFrame.filter("Calories != 'CHOIC'")

%pyspark
df.show()

%md
#### Register a temp table
Registering temp table will help us to write SQL queries on top of the data

msg.data:
Register a temp table

Registering temp table will help us to write SQL queries on top of the data

paragraphs.text:
%pyspark
df.createOrReplaceTempView("usdaTable")

%pyspark

sqlContext.sql("select * from usdaTable").show()

%pyspark
df3 = sqlContext.sql("select * from usdaTable where Calories != 'ALL GRD'")

%pyspark
df3.createOrReplaceTempView("tempTab")
df4 = sqlContext.sql("select * from tempTab where calories not like '%A%' and calories not like '%C%' and calories not like '%S%' AND calories not like '%c%' and calories not like 'PRIME'")
df4.createOrReplaceTempView("def4Tab")
sqlContext.sql("select * from def4Tab").show()

%md
#### Summary of the data
We can write SQL to calculate the cantral tendency o the data

msg.data:
Summary of the data

We can write SQL to calculate the cantral tendency o the data

paragraphs.text:
%pyspark
sqlContext.sql("select sqrt(avg(avgCal)) as stdCalories from (select power((a.calories - avg(calories) over (partition by 2 order by 2)),2) as avgCal  from def4Tab a)").show()

%md
You can use pyspark handy function to get the summary

msg.data: You can use pyspark handy function to get the summary

paragraphs.text:
%pyspark
df4.describe("calories","Protein","TotalFat").show()

%md
#### Find out the food having maximum sodium

msg.data: Find out the food having maximum sodium

paragraphs.text:
%pyspark
sqlContext.sql("select description,Sodium from def4Tab where Sodium = (select max(Sodium) from def4Tab)").show()

%md
#### Find out the details of the food having more than 10000 sodium

msg.data: Find out the details of the food having more than 10000 sodium

paragraphs.text:
%pyspark
sqlContext.sql("select * from def4tab where sodium >= 10000").show()

%md
#### Get the sodium level for caviar

%pyspark
sqlContext.sql("select * from def4tab where upper(description) like '%CAVIAR%'").show()

%md
#### Mean and standard deviation of sodium
Here you can pass column by subsetting it, can simply pass the column name and it's not case sensitive

msg.data:
Mean and standard deviation of sodium

Here you can pass column by subsetting it, can simply pass the column name and it's not case sensitive

paragraphs.text:
%pyspark
from pyspark.sql.functions import mean, min, max,stddev
df4.select(stddev(df4["Sodium"]).alias("SD"),min("Sodium").alias('MIN'),mean("sodium").alias("AVG")).show()

%md
#### Calculate the zscore using sql

%pyspark
sqlContext.sql(" select (sodium - avg)/stdev as zScore from (select sodium, stddev(Sodium) over (partition by 1 order by 1) as stdev, mean(Sodium) over (partition by 1 order by 1) as avg from def4tab)").show()

%pyspark
from pandas.tools.plotting import scatter_matrix
df5 = sqlContext.sql("select Sodium from def4tab")
pandasDF = df5.toPandas()
stuff = scatter_matrix(pandasDF, alpha=0.7, figsize=(10, 10), diagonal='kde')

%pyspark
newDF = sqlContext.sql("select T.*, case when sodium > mean(sodium) over (partition by 1 order by 1) then 1 else 0 end as highSodium,\
case when TotalFat > mean(TotalFat) over (partition by 1 order by 1) then 1 else 0 end as highFat, \
case when Protein > mean(Protein) over (partition by 1 order by 1) then 1 else 0 end as highProtein,\
case when Carbohydrate > mean(Carbohydrate) over (partition by 1 order by 1) then 1 else 0 end as highCarbs \
from def4tab T")

%md
##### Find out number of food based on sodium level

msg.data: Find out number of food based on sodium level

paragraphs.text:
%pyspark
newDF.createOrReplaceTempView("newTable")
sqlContext.sql("select case when highSodium == 1 then 'High' else 'Low' end as SodiumLevel, count(*) as count from newTable group by highSodium").show()

%md
#### Find out the number of foods got high sodium and high fat

msg.data: Find out the number of foods got high sodium and high fat

paragraphs.text:
%pyspark
sqlContext.sql("select count(1) as highSodiumHighFat from newTable where highSodium = 1 and highFat = 1").show()

%md
#### Average Iron for HighProtien and Low Protien

msg.data: Average Iron for HighProtien and Low Protien

paragraphs.text:
%pyspark
sqlContext.sql("select case when highProtein = 1 then 'High' else 'Low' end as Protien, mean(Iron) as avgIron from newTable group by highProtein").show()

%pyspark
sqlContext.sql("select case when highCarbs == 1 then 'High' else 'Low' end as Carbs, max(VitaminC) as maxVitaminC from newTable group by highCarbs ").show()
